00:02:16:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:02:16:060000.Dialogue: If I had a million guesses, I never would have gotten that.

00:02:20:090000.Speaker: Raj

00:02:43:180000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard is sorting out Chinese food.
00:02:43:180000.Speaker: Raj
00:02:43:180000.Dialogue: Sorry, it's not part of my heartwarming and personal narrative in which a humble boy from New Delhi overcame poverty and prejudice and journeyed to America to reach for the stars.

00:02:53:170000.Speaker: Howard

00:03:09:130000.Dialogue: Peer review? It's People magazine. People picked me.

What makes accidentally noticing a hunk of rock that's been traipsing around the solar system for billions of years more noteworthy than any other scientific accomplishment made by someone under 30?

00:04:33:130000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:04:35:090000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:35:090000.Dialogue: He came over last night with some pretty good news and we weren't very supportive.

00:04:40:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:40:180000.Dialogue: I sense you're trying to tell me something.

00:04:43:190000.Speaker: Howard

00:04:48:110000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:04:53:110000.Speaker: Leonard

00:04:55:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:55:030000.Dialogue: How will Raj ever reach true greatness if his friends lower the bar for him? When I was 11, my sister bought our father a World's Greatest Dad coffee mug and, frankly, the man coasted until the day he died.

00:05:08:150000.Scene: Sheldon’s office. He is making annotations on his board.
00:05:08:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:05:08:150000.Dialogue: Okay, let's try it this way. What if this People magazine thing is the best he's ever gonna achieve?

00:05:14:230000.Scene: Sheldon’s office. He is making annotations on his board.
00:05:14:230000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:05:18:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:18:110000.Dialogue: I often forget other people have limitations. It's so sad.

00:05:24:010000.Scene: Sheldon’s office. He is making annotations on his board.
00:05:24:010000.Speaker: Howard

00:05:30:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:05:30:150000.Dialogue: Now when we go in there, let's show Raj that we're happy for him.

00:05:36:210000.Speaker: Howard
00:05:36:210000.Dialogue: Well, then fake it. Look at me. I could be grinding on the fact that without my stabilizing telescope mount he never would have found that stupid, little clump of cosmic schmutz.

00:05:51:010000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:51:010000.Dialogue: Fine. What do you want me to do?

00:06:07:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:07:120000.Dialogue: We're here to see Koothrappali, not kill Batman.

00:06:19:070000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:19:070000.Dialogue: Close enough. Come on. - Hey, Raj.

00:06:25:170000.Speaker: Howard
00:06:25:170000.Dialogue: We just wanted to invite you out to dinner.

00:06:28:000000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:28:000000.Dialogue: To celebrate your 30 under 30 thing. Right, Sheldon?

00:06:35:160000.Speaker: Raj
00:06:35:160000.Dialogue: That's very nice of you. I would like that.

00:06:47:140000.Speaker: Gablehauser
00:06:47:140000.Dialogue: Boys, I've got a question for you: Who in this room discovered a star?

00:06:51:220000.Speaker: Raj
00:06:51:220000.Dialogue: Actually, 2008-NQ Sub-17 is a planetary body.

00:06:54:180000.Speaker: Gablehauser
00:06:54:180000.Dialogue: I'm not talking about you, I'm talking about me. You, my exotic young friend, are my star.

00:07:02:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:02:020000.Dialogue: But you didn't discover him. You merely noticed he was here, much like he did with 2008-NQ Sub-17. Sorry.

00:07:13:120000.Speaker: Gablehauser
00:07:13:120000.Dialogue: Boy, we've got to get you into a better office. Something more suited to your status.

00:07:17:160000.Speaker: Raj
00:07:17:160000.Dialogue: You don't have to go to any trouble.

00:07:19:090000.Speaker: Gablehauser
00:07:19:090000.Dialogue: How about Von Gerlich's old office?

00:07:21:090000.Speaker: Raj
00:07:21:090000.Dialogue: I'd rather have Fishbein's. It's bigger.

00:07:24:130000.Speaker: Howard
00:07:24:130000.Dialogue: Wait a minute, I called dibs on Fishbein's office the day he started showing up at work in his bathrobe.

00:07:30:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:30:030000.Dialogue: He gets a new office, I can't even get paper towels in the men's room? Damn, this is hard.

00:07:42:220000.Speaker: Gablehauser
00:07:42:220000.Dialogue: Let me ask you something. What do you think the business of this place is?

00:07:56:050000.Speaker: Gablehauser
00:07:56:050000.Dialogue: And this boy's picture in People magazine is gonna raise us a pile of money taller than... well, taller than you.

00:08:07:010000.Speaker: Gablehauser
00:08:07:010000.Dialogue: Who doesn't? Have you ever had lunch in the president's dining room?

00:08:13:150000.Speaker: Raj
00:08:13:150000.Dialogue: I didn't even know there was a president's dining room.

00:08:16:050000.Speaker: Gablehauser
00:08:16:050000.Dialogue: It's the same food as the cafeteria, only fresh. - Come on, little buddy.

00:08:19:040000.Speaker: Raj
00:08:19:040000.Dialogue: - Okay, big buddy. See you tonight, guys.

00:08:31:080000.Speaker: Raj
00:08:31:080000.Dialogue: So anyway, after a fantastic lunch, I was whisked off to the People magazine photo shoot... Have any of you boys ever been to a photo shoot? It's fantastic. Apparently, the camera loves me and I, it.

00:08:45:040000.Speaker: Raj
00:08:45:040000.Dialogue: They shot me in front of a starry background where I posed like this.

00:08:55:010000.Speaker: Raj
00:08:55:010000.Dialogue: They're going to digitally add a supernova. They say it's the perfect metaphor for my incandescent talent.

00:09:00:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:00:170000.Dialogue: Right, a ball of hot, flaming gas that collapses upon itself.

00:09:06:210000.Speaker: Raj
00:09:06:210000.Dialogue: Excuse me. Oh, it's my assistant, Trevor. Go for Koothrappali.

00:09:11:120000.Speaker: Howard
00:09:11:120000.Dialogue: They gave him an assistant? If I want a new pen, I have to go to the bank with wire cutters.

00:09:17:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:17:190000.Dialogue: Have we at this point met our social obligations?

00:09:21:060000.Speaker: Raj
00:09:21:060000.Dialogue: Okay, just put it on my calendar, but start thinking of a reason why I can't go. All righty? Koothrappali out.

00:09:27:220000.Speaker: Raj
00:09:27:220000.Dialogue: God bless that boy. I don't know what I'd do without him.

00:09:30:100000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:30:100000.Dialogue: You just got him this afternoon.

00:09:32:080000.Speaker: Raj
00:09:32:080000.Dialogue: Yes, but I'm finding that having a lackey suits me.

00:09:37:110000.Speaker: Raj
00:09:37:110000.Dialogue: I'm sorry. Is that politically incorrect? In India, we just call them untouchables.

00:09:45:090000.Speaker: Raj
00:09:45:090000.Dialogue: Speaking of untouchables, I've got great news for you guys.

00:09:49:160000.Speaker: Raj
00:09:49:160000.Dialogue: People magazine is having a reception this Saturday and I managed to get you invited.

00:10:05:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:05:170000.Dialogue: There's a tribe in Papua New Guinea where, when a hunter flaunts his success to the rest of the village, they kill him and drive away evil spirits with a drum made of his skin. Superstious nonsense, of course, but one can see their point.

00:10:27:030000.Speaker: Penny
00:10:27:030000.Dialogue: Here you go, Raj. You might want to drink this one slowly.

00:10:30:210000.Speaker: Raj
00:10:30:210000.Dialogue: So, Saturday night, can I count on my posse?

00:10:33:180000.Speaker: Howard
00:10:33:180000.Dialogue: Gee, I'd love to, Raj, but I can't make it.

00:10:45:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:45:220000.Dialogue: I can make it. But I won't.

00:10:50:100000.Speaker: Raj
00:10:50:100000.Dialogue: There's a reception for my magazine article on Saturday.

00:10:53:030000.Speaker: Penny
00:10:53:030000.Dialogue: And you guys aren't going? I can't believe you. Raj is celebrating a tremendous accomplishment and you're not even going to support him?

00:11:00:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:00:180000.Dialogue: A tremendous accomplishment would be if the planetary body he discovered were plummeting toward Earth and he exploded it with his mind.

00:11:08:150000.Speaker: Howard
00:11:08:150000.Dialogue: That would be cool. I'd go to that reception.

00:11:12:030000.Speaker: Penny
00:11:12:030000.Dialogue: Come on, this is huge. Raj is gonna be in People magazine, and he didn't even have to knock up one of the Spears sisters.

00:11:19:090000.Speaker: Raj
00:11:19:090000.Dialogue: Would you like to go with me?

00:11:21:150000.Speaker: Penny
00:11:21:150000.Dialogue: Of course I would. I would be honored.

00:11:30:070000.Speaker: Raj
00:11:30:070000.Dialogue: Look at that, I got a date with Penny. I can't believe it took you a whole year.

00:11:44:180000.Speaker: Raj
00:11:44:180000.Dialogue: Hey, buddy, I'm going to be in People magazine.

00:11:47:220000.Speaker: Charlie Sheen
00:11:47:220000.Dialogue: Yeah, call me when you're on the cover.
